</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,341,1194]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,341,1048,1074]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Comments.</emphasis>
Two adult females were collected so far by using pitfall traps. One was taken in April the other in October. The shiny black and white spotted congener 
<taxonomicName box="[878,957,1088,1113]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Singa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neta">
<emphasis box="[878,957,1088,1113]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">S. neta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that is known from rather diverse localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[228,293,1128,1154]" name="Israel" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Levy" box="[308,437,1128,1154]" pageId="26" pageNumber="29" refString="Levy, G. (1984) The spider genera Singa and Hypsosinga (Araneae, Araneidae) in Israel. Zoologica Scripta, 13 (2), 121 - 133." type="journal article" year="1984">
Levy 
<number box="[377,437,1128,1154]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="1984.0">1984</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) occurs also in the southern Arava but there it was found only in the salt marshes east of Yotvata and En Avrona, not on drifting sands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
